---
description: Run ShellCheck on shell script changes before finishing
globs: "**/*.sh"
alwaysApply: false
---

# ShellCheck

When creating or editing `*.sh` files in this repo:

1. Run `shellcheck -S warning -x <file>` on every changed shell script before considering the work done.
2. Fix reported issues, or add a targeted `# shellcheck disable=SC####` with a one-line reason when intentional.
3. CI runs `shellcheck -S warning -x bootstrap.sh setup.sh` on push/PR (`.github/workflows/shellcheck.yml`).
